  "text": "Because of conspicuous morphological synapomorphies, it is not difficult to recognize a specimen as part of the genus but species delimitation has not yet been firmly established and there is frequent occurrence of interspecific hybridization [CITATION_1] . The genus is easily recognized as tall herbs with long, erect and narrow leaves and the typical cylindrical-brownish inflorescence at the end of a long and unbranched axis or scape ).",
